children.text: The heater platform provided for safe access to service the heating unit is too small.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 5601 Gas Installations, clause 5.3.11 Appliances in Roof Spaces, requires that
‘A walkway is to be provided from the access point to the appliance and shall extend around the appliance to the point where access may be required for lighting or servicing’
. The Victorian Building Authority’s Technical Solution Sheet 92.05 states that
‘The location of the appliance must permit ease of access for lighting and servicing’ .
The present platform needs to be extended to provide safe access for the servicing of the heater without undue difficulty in accordance with these requirements.
